<div class="info-section" slot="info">
<h2>Base64 &amp; URL Encoder/Decoder</h2>

    <p>Base64 and percent-encoding are two different answers to the same problem: how do you transmit arbitrary data over a channel that only understands a limited set of characters? This reference covers both — what they do, when to use each, and the common mistakes that trip developers up.</p>

    <h3>Quick reference: Base64 vs URL encoding</h3>
    <table style="width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:.875rem;margin:12px 0">
        <thead>
            <tr style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);text-align:left">
